rComments: Loooooots of readings and lecture attendance is mandatory, but she's a great lecturer and if you put in the work you can easily get an A in her class. She's also super sweet and approachable, answers questions quickly, and is happy to give feedback. There is a group seminar but it's pretty easy. Would take a class with her again!!

She is two-faced. Nice to your face & then screws you over. She had 33 readings for the course, it was cumulative & she's really picky with marking. The presentations should have been easy marks. She doesn't give group evals which makes it hard to get the mark that you actually deserve. She's really unclear with her instructions. AVOID
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']
